The package @PORT@:@TARGET_TRIPLET@ provides CMake targets:

    Recommended (wire-vcpkg-registry overlay): use the per-service configs.
    They route TLS/crypto through aws-crt-cpp -> aws-c-cal -> boringssl-custom
    and do not pull in the legacy AWSSDK platformDeps shim.

    find_package(aws-cpp-sdk-core CONFIG REQUIRED)
    find_package(aws-cpp-sdk-kms  CONFIG REQUIRED)  # any selected service
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE aws-cpp-sdk-core aws-cpp-sdk-kms)

    The legacy umbrella `find_package(AWSSDK CONFIG ...)` is still installed
    for back-compat, but its platformDeps.cmake intentionally no longer
    exports `LibCrypto_*` cache variables in this overlay -- consumers
    relying on those must switch to the per-service configs above.
